    <note type="source">Smith's Dictonary: "Cratevas, Greek herbalist (π̔ιζοτόμος) who lived about the beginning of the first century B. C., as he gave the name Mithridatia to a plant in honour of Mithridates. (Plin. H. N. 25.26.) He is frequently quoted by Pliny and Dioscorides, and is mentioned by Galen...."</note>
